rails.model
Class Network

java.lang.Object
  rails.model.Network

public class Network
extends Object

This class provides the basic abstraction of rails network. A network contains a list of stations and routes connecting these stations.
Internal data structure design notes:

  • Stations are stored in their own set. This allows to represent isolated nodes in the graph.
  • Routes are grouped by their start stations. This allows to easily find routes from one station to another.

fromEncodedString

public static Network fromEncodedString(String encodedString)
Create a Network object from an encoded string. The encoded string is a list of encoded routes separated by ";". For each encoded route, it contains start station name, end station name and distance. These three components are separated by "#". See following for some examples of encoded string.
  • A#B#1
  • A#B#1;B#C#2
  • A#B#1;C#D#4;Demo#Another node#100
Unrecognized input will be ignored.

Parameters:
encodedString - String format of a network
Returns:
Network object
